@node "intro" "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

PosTit allows you to have a small iconifiable note on your WB for noting 
down information or to remind you of something. Like real post-it notes, but 
with the advantage of not leaving sticky crap all over your monitor, and with
the benefit of cut/copy/paste to and from other applications, and all this 
without having to search around your house to find a pen that works ;)

@endnode


@node "reqs" "Requirements"

@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

* AmigaOS 3.x
* MUI 
* textinput.mcc (MUI Class)
    -available from ftp.vapor.com /pub/misc/

@endnode


@node "install" "Installation"

@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

    Drag the PosTit icon to your WBStartup (or wherever you want it)
    simple ay?

@endnode


@node "usage" "Usage"

@{b}@{u}Using PosTit@{ub}@{uu}

PosTit can either run from WB, from cli, or from WBStartup.
All program settings are configured via   @{"tooltypes" link "ttypes"} and mui.

@endnode


@node "ttypes" "Tooltypes"

@{b}@{u}Tooltypes@{ub}@{uu}

The following tooltypes are available for PosTit-

FILE=<whatever> 
   set <whatever> to where you wanr PosTit to store its (tiny) note on your disk

ICONIFIED= TRUE
    PosTit will star iconified on your WB, set this to anything other than TRUE 
    and PosTit will open its window on startup.

@endnode

@node "windows" "Windows"

@{b}@{u}Windows@{ub}@{uu}

Main Window-
   Click on "Edit" to edit the note or "Hide" to iconify PosTit
   click the close gadget to quit Postit.

Edit Window-
   Here you can edit the note, all the usual textinput additions are available 
   like clipboard support etc.
   Clicking "Ok" will automatically save the text and update the note in the 
   main window,  clicking on "Cancel" or the close gadget will close the edit 
   window without altering the note.

@endnode

@node "faq" "FAQ"

@{b}@{u}FAQ@{ub}@{uu}

Why does this program exist?
- because i wanted a program to do postit notes, and the only ones i could 
  find were either too complicated or didnt use MUI.

How do i become a registered user?
- send one million pounds in used notes to me

and what do i get for my million pounds?
- the latest version and a little card with a number on it.

are you nuts? im not sending you a million pounds
- Ok, well you can use it free then, as long as you buy me a pint if you see me 
  in the pub

maybe
- cheers

@endnode

